==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water color
<hw>Wa"ter col`or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Paint.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A color ground with water and gum or other glutinous medium; a
color the vehicle of which is water; -- so called in distinction from
<contr>oil color</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It preserves its consistency when dried in a solid cake,
which is used by rubbing off a portion on a moistened palette.
<xex>Moist water colors</xex> are water colors kept in a semifluid or
pasty state in little metal tubes or pans.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A picture painted with such colors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water-colorist</ent>⟦br⟧
